COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. Robert H. HARVEY. No. 5174. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Feb. 17, 1934. Frank J. Wideman, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Charles LeForgee, of Chicago, 111., for respondent.

Before ALSCIIULER and EYANS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for petitioner, counsel for respondent consenting thereto, it is now here ordered and adjudged that this cause be docketed in this court and that the petition for a review of the decision of the United States, Board of Tax Appeals entered on October 13, 1933, be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
